h at anyone who orders any (you can get a can of soda, but expect to be seriously overcharged for it, like $5 for a can). There’s live music every night, across all genres, that’s loud enough to make conversation difficult to overhear and about 30 years of graffiti, stickers and band fliers on the wall.%0a%3c %0a%3c Supernatural%0a%3c Chances are if you’re looking for a Carthian you’ll find them at Mama’s Crow Bar, or at least you’ll find someone who knows how to find who you’re looking for, for a price of course. The apartment upstairs serves as a Movement only space for casual meetings and business. Additionally there’s a secret bolt hole in the basement that you can only get to if you know which kegs to move.%0a%3c %0a%3c Cacophony messages are intermixed with the ever present graffiti on the wall beside the stage.%0a%3c %0a%3c [&#8593; back to top]%0a%3c %0a%3c Oregon Health & Science University%0a%3c District: Southwest%0a%3c Neighborhood: Homestead%0a%3c Owned By: Ordo Dracul%0a%3c %0a%3c Spheres and Factions%0a%3c Vampire%0a%3c Ordo Dracul%0a%3c Education%0a%3c Hooks%0a%3c Medical, Nursing, and Dentistry students%0a%3c Methamphetamine%0a%3c Medical Research and Practice%0a%3c Ordo Dracul%0a%3c Embassy Seals%0a%3c Vampire (All), Private (All), Ordo Dracul (Vampire)%0a%3c The main campus, located on Marquam Hill (known by students as “Pill Hill”) is home to the university’s medical school as well as two associated hospitals. Additionally the full campus has many satellites throughout the city and partnerships with companies and research laboratories all over the state. Not only is OHSU one of the top ranked medical schools in the country with a number of thriving medical practices, but it is also a host of a number of internationally renowned researchers who serve as faculty.%0a%3c %0a%3c Supernatural%0a%3c In the basement, well past the many utilities closets that house chemicals and out of date, unworking and otherwise unused medical equipment of all kinds, and past a near labyrinth of dusty and dimly lit halls there is a door with remarkable security measures. Accessible only by a frequently changed code typed into a keypad and a dna encoded card is the Ordo Dracul’s playground. With offices for all that want them, the bowels of OHSU span across all of the buildings on campus, accessed through a number of underground halls that seem to not be on any architect’s plans of the campus. Behind the locked doors you’ll find everything that you’d need for experimentation in the work to rid yourself of the curse of vampirism and spit in the face of God. And with all of the bustle from students and overworked administrative staff, who really notices when a student or a cadaver or two go missing?%0a%3c %0a%3c [&#8593; back to top]%0a%3c %0a%3c Oregon Museum of Science and Industry%0a%3c District: Southeast%0a%3c Neighborhood: Hossford-Abernethy%0a%3c Owned By: Ordo Dracul%0a%3c %0a%3c Spheres and Factions%0a%3c - Vampire%0a%3c - Mage%0a%3c - Education%0a%3c - Business%0a%3c Hooks%0a%3c - Science%0a%3c - Industry%0a%3c - School field trips%0a%3c - Medical,%0a%3c - Nursing,%0a%3c - Dentistry%0a%3c - Students%0a%3c - Methamphetamine Medical Research and Practice%0a%3c - Ordo Dracul%0a%3c - OSHU Elysium%0a%3c - Guardian of the Veil%0a%3c Embassy Seals%0a%3c Vampire (All), Mage (All), Mortal (All)%0a%3c The Oregon Museum of Science and Industry (OMSI) contains three auditoriums, including a large-screen theater, planetarium, and exhibition halls with a variety of hands-on permanent exhibits focused on natural sciences, industry, and technology. Transient exhibits span a wider range of disciplines.%0a%3c %0a%3c Supernatural%0a%3c To the untrained eye many of the displays, though fascinating are completely mundane. But to those with an eye for such things, there is no doubt of the influence of the Elder Dragon’s touch here and there. Make no mistake, the OMSI is as much a shrine to the ingenuity and experimentation of the Dragons as it is to the mortal realm.%0a%3c %0a%3c [&#8593; back to top]%0a%3c %0a%3c Ross Island%0a%3c District: Southeast%0a%3c Neighborhood: Brooklyn%0a%3c Owned By: The Circle of the Crone%0a%3c %0a%3c Spheres and Factions%0a%3c Vampire%0a%3c Shadow%0a%3c Hooks%0a%3c The Dark Mother%0a%3c Pain, Blood, Magic%0a%3c Nature%0a%3c Privacy%0a%3c Embassy Seals%0a%3c Vampire Territory (All), Dangerous (All), The Circle of the Crone (Vampires), Restricted (Vampires)%0a%3c %0a%3c Talisman%0a%3c There are four islands in the middle of the Willamette River and Ross Island is the main island. Mined for years by the Ross Island Sand and Gravel (RISG) it was purchased recently and turned into a private nature preserve. There is no access to Ross Island from the other islands, the only way there is by boat. There is a single dock that is patrolled by armed private security and visitors are quietly encouraged to quickly move on.%0a%3c %0a%3c Supernatural%0a%3c Ross Island has been the home for The Circle of the Crone’s rituals and festivals for as long as they have been residents of the city of Portland. For a long time The Acolytes controlled the island’s ritual area through blood magic but recently found it easier to deal with the prospectors and miners by purchasing the island entirely and closing it off from the public. Now with privacy the island has turned from nature preserve to horror show of witchcraft. Hidden by the thick canopy of leaves and the close press of trees are piles of stripped bone, their origins unidentifiable. There are small sticks and bones tied together as talisman in a variety of shapes as wards and protections that hang from limbs, draped with vines. There are pools of blood mixed with ash and herb. The trunks of many trees and many of the larger stones have been either painted or carved, depicting the visage of Goddesses, other deity, and bodies in a plethora of positions denoting expressions ranging from agony to ecstasy and everything in between. In the center of the island there is a circular clearing, the grass underfoot having been burned away. In the center of the clearing sits a stone table, the stained top worn smooth by decades of use.%0a%3c %0a%3c [&#8593; back to top]%0a%3c %0a%3c The Dragon Den%0a%3c District: Northwest%0a%3c Neighborhood: Arlington Heights%0a%3c Owned By: Diana Martin%0a%3c %0a%3c Spheres and Factions%0a%3c Vampire%0a%3c Invictus%0a%3c High Society%0a%3c Business%0a%3c City Hall/Government%0a%3c Crime%0a%3c Hooks%0a%3c Money%0a%3c Power%0a%3c Movers and Shakers%0a%3c Embassy Seals%0a%3c Vampire (All), Invitation Only (All), Invictus (Vampire)%0a%3c %0a%3c A semi-private booth%0a%3c Housed in what was the front parlor of the Feng Mansion in Arlington Heights, The Dragon Den is an elite social club where the rich and influential meet with one another to socialize, play the political games of the wealthy, and cut deals. Profit, by any means necessary, whether social or financial, is its stock-in-trade. The room is furnished in dark woods and lush leathers with private booths for meetings to be had away from prying ears.%0a%3c %0a%3c Supernatural%0a%3c Though this is a Vampire controlled property it is open to all Factions of the city, by invitation. Those who show up without are quietly but quickly escorted out by large and capable guards and given a firm suggestion that they never come back, lest they invite more severe consequences. Fortunately, though, invitations are not hard to come by for those who can make good conversation with its owner, Diana Martin.%0a%3c %0a%3c %0a%3c [&#8593; back to top]%0a%3c %0a%3c The Grotto%0a%3c District: Central%0a%3c Neighborhood: Madison South%0a%3c Owned By: Lancea et Sanctum%0a%3c %0a%3c Spheres and Factions%0a%3c Vampire%0a%3c Lancea et Sanctum%0a%3c Hooks%0a%3c Catholics%0a%3c Tourists%0a%3c Guilt%0a%3c Oh my!%0a%3c Embassy Seals%0a%3c Vampire (All), Neutral Ground (All), Lancea et Sanctum (Vampire)%0a%3c Unlike your traditional church the National Sanctuary of our Sorrowful Mother (or the Grotto as it’s popularly known as) is an outdoor shrine, sanctuary and botanical garden. Comprised of 62 acres of meticulously kept green space, just minutes from downtown, the Grotto is a draw for both tourists and locals of all faiths and creeds. The heart of the Grotto is a rock cave carved into the base of a 110-foot cliff. A life-size marble replica of Michelangelo’s Pietà is featured in its center.%0a%3c %0a%3c Supernatural%0a%3c Off the beaten path, shrouded by a dense grouping of fir trees where it’s impossible to find unless you know where to look, is another cave that’s been carved into the cliff. This one however is used as a meeting space for the Lancea et Sanctum and is also home of the city’s frequent Midnight Mass. The space is stark, there is no sight of the lush green, and while there are pews for the masses they are rough carved from stone, without the comfort of polish or smoothed edges. Here is there no sign of the comfort of the Blessed Mother Mary, there is only the cold fact of God’s wrath.%0a%3c %0a%3c [&#8593; back to top]%0a%3c %0a%3c ThermoFischer Scientific Office%0a%3c District: Southeast%0a%3c Neighborhood: Hosford-Abernethy%0a%3c Owned By: Ordo Dracul%0a%3c %0a%3c Spheres and Factions%0a%3c Vampire%0a%3c Ordo Dracul%0a%3c Business%0a%3c Hooks%0a%3c Research%0a%3c Development%0a%3c Bio-engineering%0a%3c Embassy Seals%0a%3c Vampire (All), Ordo Dracul (Vampire) Off Limits (Vampire) Property of Constantine (Ordo Dracul)%0a%3c Thermo Fisher Scientific Inc. is the world leader in serving science. Their’s is a mission to make the world healthier, cleaner and safer. Thermo Fisher has offices, research labs and distribution centers around the world though their Portland office seems home to some of the most promising advances in science and technology.%0a%3c %0a%3c Supernatural%0a%3c Though the bulk of the Dragons have their offices and laboratories at OHSU Thermo Fisher Scientific belongs entirely and totally to Constantine. It is the unfortunate Kindred that finds out what it is exactly that he does there.%0a%3c %0a%3c [&#8593; back to top]%0a%3c %0a%3c Directory: Vampire the Requiem%0a%3c About the Venue	History	Society	Locations	Player Guide%0a%3c %0a%3c Portland, OR %0a%3c Districts%0a%3c %0a%3c Changeling %0a%3c Player Guide%0a%3c %0a%3c Mage %0a%3c Player Guide%0a%3c %0a%3c Mortal %0a%3c Player Guide%0a%3c %0a%3c Vampire %0a%3c Player Guide%0a%3c %0a%3c Werewolf %0a%3c Player Guide%0a%3c Edit - History - Print - Recent Changes - Search%0a%3c Page last modified on August 21, 2017, at 05:54 PM%0a%3c The Storytelling System, Beast the Primordial, Changeling the Lost, Chronicles of Darkness, Demon the Descent, Mage the Awakening, Vampire the Requiem, and Werewolf the Forsaken ©2014-2016 CCP hf and published by Onyx Path Publishing.%0a%3c Produced by Jeff Vandenberg. Layout and Design by Jill Arden ©2016%0a\ No newline at end of file%0a
